WEBVTT

00:01.784 --> 00:03.394
COOKE:
I came here merely to store

00:03.481 --> 00:06.615
-excess barrels.
-And if you agree to my terms,

00:06.702 --> 00:09.009
you will leave
with a French wife.

00:09.096 --> 00:11.576
Previously onBarkskins...

00:11.663 --> 00:13.274
GAY BILL:
I should like
to have those barrels

00:13.361 --> 00:14.753
of pistols you promised.

00:14.840 --> 00:16.059
They are lost to me.

00:16.146 --> 00:17.843
Is that so?

00:17.930 --> 00:20.672
-You left this.
-CROSS: Let me go.

00:20.759 --> 00:22.587
I'll walk into the woods
and begone.

00:22.674 --> 00:24.154
You've lost your mind, Randall.

00:24.241 --> 00:26.374
[grunts]

00:26.461 --> 00:29.072
BOUCHARD:
When I have settled
this Iroquois matter,

00:29.159 --> 00:33.120
you and I,
we might go for a stroll.

00:33.207 --> 00:34.991
Tell him I saw what the ram's
insides spoke of.

00:35.078 --> 00:36.601
What are you talking about?

00:36.688 --> 00:39.604
-Tell him I saw his end.
-Get out!

00:39.691 --> 00:41.302
You are still Wyandot.

00:41.389 --> 00:43.043
Leave Theo with us.

00:43.130 --> 00:44.827
Fight for your place
with Trepagny.

00:45.958 --> 00:47.047
Please.

00:50.702 --> 00:52.878
RENE:
The Englishman
wants us to come for them.

00:52.965 --> 00:54.358
It's a trap.

00:54.445 --> 00:55.881
BOUCHARD:
They want French.

00:55.968 --> 00:57.013
We send

00:57.100 --> 00:58.884
an Englishman.

00:58.971 --> 01:01.104
Pistols for the dead.

01:27.652 --> 01:29.654
♪ ♪

01:38.533 --> 01:40.491
[man panting]

01:42.537 --> 01:44.495
Pitié.

02:10.956 --> 02:12.915
GAY BILL:
What's this one on about?

02:14.960 --> 02:16.614
He wants mercy.

02:17.746 --> 02:18.921
GAY BILL:
Does he?

02:21.228 --> 02:22.533
I'll hear your last words,
French.

02:30.019 --> 02:31.673
Come on, now, friend.

02:31.760 --> 02:34.589
What else have you achieved
besides skinning pelts

02:34.676 --> 02:36.634
and trudging through snow?

02:49.952 --> 02:51.519
Now, there's a life's work.

02:51.606 --> 02:53.434
What else?

02:53.521 --> 02:55.087
He's given it.

02:55.175 --> 02:57.177
No. No, he's got more to say.

03:09.798 --> 03:12.192
We are all animals.

03:12.279 --> 03:14.237
Now there's a final truth.

03:14.324 --> 03:16.413
Give it if you're
going to give it.

03:25.901 --> 03:28.208
I will guide the wood
into your heart.

03:31.080 --> 03:32.647
[gasps]

03:54.930 --> 03:58.107
Dead man's ring
will bring dead man's luck.

04:11.512 --> 04:13.427
-[Iroquois whooping]
-[gunshots]

04:16.430 --> 04:18.388
[woman screaming]

04:24.525 --> 04:25.917
[woman crying]

04:27.919 --> 04:30.748
Help me.

04:34.012 --> 04:35.971
Is this what you wanted?

04:49.550 --> 04:51.856
Enough. We're done
killing innocent people.

04:51.943 --> 04:53.728
Done?

04:53.815 --> 04:55.947
A Company man's work
is never done, Hamish.

04:56.034 --> 04:57.949
We aren't until every
French settlement is torched.

04:58.036 --> 05:01.257
She has no stake in this.
Let her go.

05:01.344 --> 05:03.477
She stays here.
You're gonna remind Mr. Cooke

05:03.564 --> 05:05.827
of the deal he struck
for the pistols.

05:06.958 --> 05:09.352
And when he has his pistols?

05:09.439 --> 05:12.007
He's agreed to go north,

05:12.094 --> 05:13.661
take the settlement
at Pont-Rouge.

05:13.748 --> 05:16.011
Wobik's well-defended.
Even he knows that.

05:16.098 --> 05:18.666
-I'll go with you.
-HAMISH: No.

05:18.753 --> 05:21.146
This is my burden to bear.

05:21.233 --> 05:23.061
Stay here, watch the girl.

05:24.324 --> 05:26.413
You will control them.

05:28.980 --> 05:31.766
Your Indian will make sure
she's safe until your return.

05:31.853 --> 05:33.202
Hopefully.

05:38.773 --> 05:40.731
♪ ♪

05:52.656 --> 05:54.615
-[door opens]
-[bell jingles]

05:56.834 --> 05:58.009
[exhales]

06:00.098 --> 06:03.363
-Captain.
-Mathilde. Delphine.

06:03.450 --> 06:06.191
There is a fierce,
damp cold this morning.

06:06.278 --> 06:08.280
-It will be an early winter.
-Mm.

06:08.368 --> 06:12.197
If it is another walk you're
after, Captain, I am busy today.

06:12.284 --> 06:14.591
I am preparing Monsieur
Trepagny's wedding feast.

06:14.678 --> 06:16.288
And it is a feast

06:16.376 --> 06:18.682
that will put the harvest
celebration to shame.

06:18.769 --> 06:21.598
That is the exact topic
I came to speak to you about.

06:21.685 --> 06:24.601
Ah. Outside, if you must.

06:32.609 --> 06:34.306
[quietly]:
There is a mighty fondness

06:34.394 --> 06:36.352
lurking in that girl
for rabbits.

06:37.658 --> 06:39.616
MATHILDE:
Renardette.

06:39.703 --> 06:42.663
Tell Captain Bouchard
what you have named it.

06:42.750 --> 06:44.099
Bouchard.

06:44.186 --> 06:46.406
Oui?
[chuckles]

06:46.493 --> 06:49.887
That is a proper name
for such a beast.

06:49.974 --> 06:52.673
Hopefully it doesn't
end up in the cook pot.

07:00.898 --> 07:02.683
Has she told you
where her parents are?

07:02.770 --> 07:05.860
I... She will tell it
when she is ready.

07:05.947 --> 07:08.079
For now,

07:08.166 --> 07:11.343
I keep her engaged
in simple tasks.

07:11.431 --> 07:14.303
Mathilde, now is not the time
to be traveling to Trepagny's,

07:14.390 --> 07:17.262
with the Iroquois about.

07:17.349 --> 07:19.787
We will be with the intendant
and his men.

07:19.874 --> 07:23.660
Besides, Mother Sabrine
has returned the dead

07:23.747 --> 07:26.097
and Mr. Cooke
has proved his mettle.

07:26.184 --> 07:28.186
I do believe

07:28.273 --> 07:30.972
the Iroquois matter
is behind us.

07:31.059 --> 07:33.670
I am going to Trepagny's.

07:33.757 --> 07:35.846
He has hired me.
That is the end of it.

07:35.933 --> 07:38.283
[sighs, grunts]

07:38.370 --> 07:41.417
Then I will escort you to
this cursed wedding celebration.

07:41.504 --> 07:44.768
See that you get there safe.

07:44.855 --> 07:46.640
Your clothes will need a wash.

07:48.511 --> 07:49.991
I'll see to that.

07:50.078 --> 07:52.036
Good.

07:52.123 --> 07:54.604
Now leave me to my business.

07:54.691 --> 07:55.779
[smack]

08:24.504 --> 08:26.157
[humming a tune]

08:34.470 --> 08:36.516
You were gone a long time.

08:39.388 --> 08:41.956
Yes, I-I stopped
to watch a bird.

08:43.435 --> 08:44.828
A bird.

08:45.960 --> 08:47.527
A cunning black bird.

08:47.614 --> 08:49.790
It was going after a woodchuck.

08:51.095 --> 08:53.533
And after, where did you go?

08:56.013 --> 08:58.581
If you wish,
I will fetch Rene Sel

08:58.668 --> 09:00.801
down from his work
so you can ask him.

09:00.888 --> 09:03.064
Or perhaps Mari can
bring the basket herself

09:03.151 --> 09:05.675
so you can peck at her
with your questions.

09:05.762 --> 09:07.808
I only have one question
that matters.

09:09.810 --> 09:13.074
Have you found
a solution to Mari?

09:14.336 --> 09:15.642
No, not yet.

09:17.513 --> 09:18.862
But look, we have these baskets

09:18.949 --> 09:22.126
of well-prepared food each day.

09:22.213 --> 09:24.433
Mari does not cross your path.

09:24.520 --> 09:26.566
She is in the cabin,
you're here,

09:26.653 --> 09:28.611
in the manor house.

09:30.308 --> 09:32.180
It works, Melissande.

09:42.016 --> 09:43.931
I will not banish her.

09:44.018 --> 09:47.369
Her presence
is a challenge to me.

09:47.456 --> 09:50.633
Do you own the land?

09:50.720 --> 09:53.897
I look and see smoke from her
cabin and I know she is here.

09:53.984 --> 09:55.899
Well, there is no dark magic

09:55.986 --> 09:57.988
to undo the past.

09:58.075 --> 10:00.817
My ancestors tried.
They were burned at the stake.

10:00.904 --> 10:03.994
I don't wish to undo the past,
just fix the present.

10:05.126 --> 10:06.475
[sighs]

10:08.520 --> 10:10.566
What if you...

10:10.653 --> 10:13.395
gave her to Rene?

10:14.483 --> 10:17.007
He has eyes for her.

10:17.094 --> 10:19.444
I've seen it.

10:19.531 --> 10:22.491
This is all I want
for our wedding celebration.

10:23.753 --> 10:25.320
To know that we are bound

10:25.407 --> 10:27.583
and there is no woman
with a claim on you.

10:28.758 --> 10:31.108
So it is a clever fix.

10:31.195 --> 10:33.763
-Well, it is afix.
-Good.

10:33.850 --> 10:36.026
Then talk to him.

10:39.116 --> 10:41.118
[grunts]

10:48.996 --> 10:50.998
Monsieur Sel!

10:53.043 --> 10:55.393
You should come up.
Have a look.

10:55.480 --> 10:57.439
No.

10:57.526 --> 11:01.661
I will save it for the ceremony.

11:01.748 --> 11:03.793
Melissande and I will
see it together

11:03.880 --> 11:06.100
as we look out over the Doma,

11:06.187 --> 11:08.668
properly bound, man and wife.

11:08.755 --> 11:10.495
It will be my gift to her.

11:10.582 --> 11:12.497
That is a good gift, sir.

11:12.584 --> 11:15.022
Yes.

11:15.109 --> 11:18.025
There is another she asks of me.

11:18.112 --> 11:20.941
Uh, it is something
you can help me with.

11:21.028 --> 11:22.986
I'll come down.

11:26.381 --> 11:28.209
Yes, the favor?

11:30.298 --> 11:33.214
Say it and it shall be done.

11:33.301 --> 11:35.695
You came here to New France

11:35.782 --> 11:37.305
in search of land

11:37.392 --> 11:39.046
and to build a family.

11:39.133 --> 11:40.830
Yes.

11:43.485 --> 11:46.793
What if I were
to give you that land?

11:46.880 --> 11:49.447
And in return,

11:49.534 --> 11:51.798
you take Mari to be your wife.

11:57.891 --> 12:01.111
I have seen the way
you look at her.

12:01.198 --> 12:04.549
-Supping together...
-No.

12:04.636 --> 12:08.379
-I have never looked
upon her like that.
-Do not lie.

12:08.466 --> 12:11.034
She is a woman, you are a man.

12:11.121 --> 12:13.297
You have looked at her,
is it not so?

12:18.955 --> 12:20.914
Yes.

12:23.003 --> 12:24.134
I have looked.

12:25.266 --> 12:27.311
Then she could be your wife.

12:29.096 --> 12:31.054
But she is yours.

12:31.141 --> 12:33.840
And she will never agree to a
match she has not made herself.

12:33.927 --> 12:36.668
She is not mine.

12:36.756 --> 12:38.105
She never was.

12:39.846 --> 12:42.587
I simply wish to know
that she is taken care of,

12:42.674 --> 12:45.503
not tossed from the Doma,

12:45.590 --> 12:49.333
as my dear Melissande
would have me do.

12:49.420 --> 12:51.771
Land, Monsieur Sel.

12:51.858 --> 12:55.426
I will give you the cabin
and all the land around.

12:55.513 --> 12:57.298
Perhaps even a lake.

13:01.911 --> 13:04.305
Say you will talk to her.

13:06.307 --> 13:08.309
Yes.

13:11.312 --> 13:12.704
I will talk to her.

13:15.142 --> 13:17.100
Good man.

13:19.624 --> 13:21.583
It is better this way.

13:40.080 --> 13:42.038
-[knocking]
-[clears throat]

13:49.524 --> 13:51.439
Shall I come in?

13:51.526 --> 13:53.745
Yes.
Yes, of course.

13:53.833 --> 13:55.835
Yes, we mustn't waste a minute.

13:58.750 --> 14:01.841
I've... prepared tea.

14:07.455 --> 14:09.805
Oh, please, I...
Let me do it.

14:09.892 --> 14:12.416
No, of course not.
You're my guest.

14:12.503 --> 14:15.158
And, uh, a good man serves.

14:28.737 --> 14:30.739
Merci.

14:47.843 --> 14:49.192
Something wrong?

14:49.279 --> 14:50.759
Oh, no.

14:52.282 --> 14:55.807
Everything is fine
and beautiful.

14:55.895 --> 14:59.246
This feels, uh, very formal.

15:00.812 --> 15:02.162
Yes, you're right,
this is not, uh,

15:02.249 --> 15:03.728
appropriate for our purposes.

15:03.815 --> 15:05.817
Uh, an interaction.

15:07.732 --> 15:09.169
Which is not business.

15:09.256 --> 15:11.780
[chuckles softly]

15:11.867 --> 15:14.391
Might there be a more, uh,

15:14.478 --> 15:16.828
comfortable place for us to sit?

15:18.178 --> 15:20.093
I have a fire.

15:20.180 --> 15:23.618
-Shall we sit there?
-Uh, yes.

15:24.706 --> 15:26.664
I will take the tea.

15:47.468 --> 15:49.383
I need a word with Cooke.

15:49.470 --> 15:50.993
He's engaged at the moment.

15:51.080 --> 15:53.039
Unengage him.

15:53.126 --> 15:55.041
He should like to hear
what I have to say.

15:57.478 --> 15:58.827
Go on.

16:10.926 --> 16:12.928
[Cooke exhales]

16:23.983 --> 16:25.941
Mathilde said we should talk.

16:27.029 --> 16:29.989
Mathilde. Yes.

16:30.076 --> 16:32.948
We should see where
our-our paths might intersect.

16:33.035 --> 16:35.298
I would like that very much.

16:35.385 --> 16:37.648
First, might I show you
something?

16:42.001 --> 16:45.395
It is a claw. Of a tiger.

16:48.529 --> 16:50.661
This came to me in a barrel

16:50.748 --> 16:54.013
from a Dutchman
with contacts in China.

16:56.276 --> 16:58.017
It is beautiful.

16:58.104 --> 17:01.933
You see, the tiger...

17:02.021 --> 17:04.849
is the lord of all creatures.

17:04.936 --> 17:06.895
Men worship them,

17:06.982 --> 17:10.420
build temples, light candles
to their wickedness.

17:10.507 --> 17:12.857
[laughs softly]

17:12.944 --> 17:14.859
That's impossible to imagine.

17:14.946 --> 17:16.861
Oh, but the world
is much smaller

17:16.948 --> 17:19.038
than you think, Delphine.

17:20.126 --> 17:23.216
It comes to me in barrels.

17:23.303 --> 17:24.782
Pieces of it.

17:24.869 --> 17:28.047
And I send pieces
of this place back.

17:30.136 --> 17:32.094
Give me your hand.

17:36.620 --> 17:37.795
You see...

17:40.233 --> 17:42.061
...the world rests
in the palm of your hand.

17:45.107 --> 17:47.240
Is there anything about me
you would like to know?

17:47.327 --> 17:49.938
Well, I hope that we may

17:50.025 --> 17:53.028
come to know one another,
in time.

17:56.814 --> 17:58.338
We are all

17:58.425 --> 18:00.992
criminally strange
to one another.

18:01.080 --> 18:03.821
That is what I believe.

18:03.908 --> 18:05.084
Do you think so?

18:09.175 --> 18:11.873
Each day we reveal
ourselves anew.

18:11.960 --> 18:13.875
That is what I believe.

18:13.962 --> 18:17.052
Yes. Indeed.

18:22.275 --> 18:24.799
Would you care to take
a trip to the Orient with me

18:24.886 --> 18:26.279
to see a tiger, Delphine?

18:26.366 --> 18:28.977
-[door opens, closes]
-CHARLES: Sir?

18:29.064 --> 18:30.979
What?

18:31.066 --> 18:32.763
Oh...

18:32.850 --> 18:34.635
I'm busy, Charles.

18:34.722 --> 18:38.595
There is something that, uh,
requires your attention.

18:40.206 --> 18:42.730
I'm sorry.

18:42.817 --> 18:44.601
Excuse me.

18:48.257 --> 18:50.390
[door opens, closes]

18:58.354 --> 19:00.269
Mr. Goames.
What brings you here?

19:01.314 --> 19:03.620
I shall be direct.

19:05.318 --> 19:07.233
The pistols in exchange
for your life.

19:09.583 --> 19:10.975
Sorry, tell me,
when did you become

19:11.062 --> 19:12.542
errand boy for Bill Selby?

19:14.240 --> 19:16.372
It should be a comfort to you
that I am here,

19:16.459 --> 19:19.375
as it is Bill's plan to ambush
you and cut your throat.

19:21.072 --> 19:23.510
Well, pistols can
be had elsewhere.

19:25.381 --> 19:27.253
Mr. Selby knows this.

19:27.340 --> 19:29.820
You should know that failing to
do good on your part of the deal

19:29.907 --> 19:31.822
will result in Selby
and the Iroquois

19:31.909 --> 19:33.781
putting Wobik to the torch.

19:33.868 --> 19:35.739
Now,

19:35.826 --> 19:37.828
I wish to avoid that.

19:37.915 --> 19:39.743
I wish to save
the good people of Wobik

19:39.830 --> 19:43.007
and for you to die.

19:43.094 --> 19:46.489
Well, the intendant has called
for further reinforcements,

19:46.576 --> 19:49.536
so, rest assured,
Wobik will be well-defended.

19:49.623 --> 19:51.407
If they don't get the pistols,

19:51.494 --> 19:54.193
they will save you
to last, Cooke.

19:54.280 --> 19:56.282
They will peel off your eyelids

19:56.369 --> 19:58.414
and make you eat them.

19:58.501 --> 20:02.244
And then they will
lash you to a rock,

20:02.331 --> 20:05.204
and let the sun burn your eyes
out of your head.

20:07.031 --> 20:09.208
If you go back on your deal,

20:09.295 --> 20:11.732
I cannot stop them.

20:11.819 --> 20:13.821
Mr. Cooke no longer
has the pistols.

20:13.908 --> 20:16.171
You are both full of lies.

20:16.258 --> 20:17.999
COOKE:
Yes.

20:18.086 --> 20:20.219
As are we all.

20:20.306 --> 20:22.569
It is truths

20:22.656 --> 20:24.701
that we pay dearly for,
Mr. Goames.

20:24.788 --> 20:28.314
Here is a truth:
you made a deal for your life.

20:28.401 --> 20:29.924
Yes, but I make many deals.

20:30.011 --> 20:32.013
Soon I will have a deal
for a French wife.

20:33.319 --> 20:35.582
Shall I summon Captain Bouchard?

20:35.669 --> 20:37.627
No, thank you, Charles.

20:37.714 --> 20:39.150
Mr. Goames is a smart man.

20:39.238 --> 20:40.587
No need to involve the captain.

20:40.674 --> 20:43.677
I can be found
out by the creek path.

20:43.764 --> 20:46.723
The Iroquois have
set up camp nearby.

20:48.421 --> 20:50.466
[door opens]

20:51.685 --> 20:52.642
[door closes]

21:13.315 --> 21:15.274
Renardette!

21:18.233 --> 21:20.279
Renardette.

21:25.371 --> 21:26.589
Monsieur Bouchard.

21:37.252 --> 21:38.427
Mr. Goames?

21:41.256 --> 21:43.693
-Has Cooke reconsidered?
-No.

21:43.780 --> 21:45.913
Then I shall not waste
another minute of my time.

21:46.000 --> 21:48.524
-Lives are at stake.
-That is a shame,
as a few minutes

21:48.611 --> 21:52.049
might provide you
with the pistols you seek.

21:53.181 --> 21:55.618
-You have them?
-Cooke does.

21:55.705 --> 21:57.577
He intends to turn
them over to Bouchard.

21:58.708 --> 22:00.623
And you would stop this?

22:00.710 --> 22:02.669
For a price.

22:04.758 --> 22:07.151
I will hear your offer,

22:07.238 --> 22:10.329
keeping in mind
the risk I am taking.

22:12.026 --> 22:14.289
Bring them to me at the camp,

22:14.376 --> 22:15.943
and we will discuss terms.

22:16.030 --> 22:18.293
I will not barter with savages.

22:22.079 --> 22:24.038
This is our deal.

22:24.125 --> 22:27.868
The path behind the creek.

22:27.955 --> 22:30.914
A lookout will bring you
into the camp.

22:34.048 --> 22:36.572
Then I should like
some coin now.

22:36.659 --> 22:38.618
For my end of the risk.

22:47.670 --> 22:50.020
-[coins jingle]
-The rest upon delivery.

22:50.107 --> 22:53.372
See that you come alone.

22:53.459 --> 22:55.417
Bonne chance.

23:02.729 --> 23:04.687
[dogs barking]

23:25.665 --> 23:28.145
[exhales]
What happened?

23:28.232 --> 23:30.147
Bill.

23:30.234 --> 23:32.149
The girl?

23:32.236 --> 23:34.238
She's all right, for now.

23:35.675 --> 23:36.937
Did you get the pistols?

23:38.852 --> 23:42.029
Take the girl and leave.
I'll manage the rest.

23:42.116 --> 23:43.857
Manage them?

23:44.945 --> 23:46.033
Now go.

23:52.692 --> 23:54.171
GAY BILL:
Sneaking off to read some verse,

23:54.258 --> 23:56.565
Mr. Kirkpatrick?

23:57.697 --> 24:00.743
-Dryden.
-Dryden.

24:00.830 --> 24:03.572
I should like to hear
some of that.

24:03.659 --> 24:04.834
Is there one you favor?

24:06.575 --> 24:09.317
You're welcome to join me.

24:09.404 --> 24:10.449
HAMISH:
Let him go.

24:10.536 --> 24:13.626
We have much to discuss.

24:13.713 --> 24:16.498
I suppose so. Perhaps later.

24:20.459 --> 24:24.375
Oh, Mr. Kirkpatrick,
don't read yourself out.

24:26.639 --> 24:28.771
Where are the pistols?

24:28.858 --> 24:30.730
Cooke's man is bringing them.

24:30.817 --> 24:32.993
Well, it's good that Cooke
has found his part of the deal.

24:33.080 --> 24:35.561
No. He's not found
his part of the deal.

24:35.648 --> 24:38.651
Cooke's man
is getting them for us.

24:38.738 --> 24:40.435
Can this man be trusted?

24:40.522 --> 24:43.917
The English, the French,

24:44.004 --> 24:45.614
your precious Company--

24:45.701 --> 24:48.225
none of you can be trusted.

24:48.312 --> 24:50.967
They'll likely send more French.

24:51.054 --> 24:52.752
Soldiers this time,
instead of nuns.

24:52.839 --> 24:55.711
No.

24:55.798 --> 24:58.366
It is as I say.
Just Cooke's man.

24:58.453 --> 25:00.977
I think Mr. Goames
is a man of his word.

25:05.808 --> 25:08.463
Make sure he's alone
and with the pistols.

25:19.518 --> 25:21.258
[insects trilling]

25:30.093 --> 25:32.487
If it's food you are after,
it will have to wait.

25:32.574 --> 25:34.533
No.

25:34.620 --> 25:36.709
I wish to have a word.

25:36.796 --> 25:39.712
[sighs]
Go on then.

25:39.799 --> 25:42.105
-It's Trepagny.
-It is always Trepagny.

25:42.192 --> 25:44.064
Mari, please.

25:44.151 --> 25:46.109
Listen to me.

25:50.723 --> 25:51.898
Out with it.

25:51.985 --> 25:54.553
He has asked something of me.

26:00.036 --> 26:02.909
He believes
we could be together.

26:05.128 --> 26:06.521
As husband and wife.

26:10.090 --> 26:11.265
He told you this?

26:12.875 --> 26:15.965
It is not as it sounds.

26:16.052 --> 26:18.359
Go on then.

26:18.446 --> 26:20.404
Tell me more, and I will

26:20.491 --> 26:22.842
tell you how it sounds.

26:22.929 --> 26:24.887
He has made me an offer
of land in return.

26:24.974 --> 26:26.367
For taking me off of his hands.

26:26.454 --> 26:28.674
This could be a new start
for both of us.

26:30.153 --> 26:33.156
A chance for you
to stay in the cabin

26:33.243 --> 26:34.375
and for us

26:34.462 --> 26:36.595
to be together.

26:36.682 --> 26:38.597
This is his idea?

26:41.251 --> 26:42.818
It is not so bad an offer.

26:57.267 --> 26:59.095
Could you take a man such as me?

27:02.664 --> 27:04.492
We could be a good match.

27:08.975 --> 27:10.367
I will think on it.

27:28.603 --> 27:31.475
♪ ♪

27:50.538 --> 27:51.887
MARI:
Bouchard.

27:56.457 --> 27:58.459
It's fine, I work for Mr. Cooke.

28:14.693 --> 28:15.998
Come on.

28:42.372 --> 28:43.765
MELISSANDE:
What did she say?

28:43.852 --> 28:46.725
TREPAGNY:
Rene Sel is proposing a fix.

28:46.812 --> 28:50.076
MELISSANDE:
She would be smart to agree,
or you must cast her off.

28:50.163 --> 28:53.427
That is how I see it.

28:53.514 --> 28:55.864
I see only you in that dress

28:55.951 --> 28:59.520
and how you will look
floating above the trees.

29:05.308 --> 29:07.876
I will have her decision
before Mathilde

29:07.963 --> 29:09.356
and the rest
of the guests arrive.

29:09.443 --> 29:12.881
Yes, of course.

29:12.968 --> 29:16.972
Now step into the light that
I might see the glow of you.

29:23.196 --> 29:25.372
No.

29:25.459 --> 29:28.244
I will be alone tonight.

29:37.471 --> 29:39.778
[grunts, exhales]

29:39.865 --> 29:42.476
Renardette!

29:42.563 --> 29:45.261
Come inside!

29:45.348 --> 29:47.916
Oh. It's late.

29:53.400 --> 29:55.532
Renardette.

30:07.240 --> 30:08.937
Renardette?

30:18.512 --> 30:20.862
She was watching the barrels
for me. That was her job.

30:20.949 --> 30:22.385
-Cooke's barrels?
-Yeah. Yes.

30:22.472 --> 30:24.083
-What was in them?
-I don't know.

30:24.170 --> 30:26.650
Well, then let's ask Mr. Cooke.

30:28.435 --> 30:30.741
Cooke, you scheming bastard.

30:30.829 --> 30:33.744
What new offense are you here
to accuse me of?

30:33.832 --> 30:35.877
Renardette has gone missing.
Taken!

30:35.964 --> 30:38.706
I set her to watch your barrels.

30:38.793 --> 30:41.970
-Now they are ransacked.
-The barrels are empty?

30:42.057 --> 30:45.147
Pray tell, Mr. Cooke,
what was in those barrels?

30:45.234 --> 30:46.714
Nothing.

30:50.022 --> 30:52.763
Come now, Mr. Cooke.

30:52.851 --> 30:54.026
S-Salt.

30:54.113 --> 30:55.766
Brick.

30:57.072 --> 30:59.248
Stop! We are wasting time.

30:59.335 --> 31:01.729
Renardette is missing,
that is what matters.

31:04.297 --> 31:06.516
Pistols.

31:09.128 --> 31:11.130
The barrels were packed
with pistols.

31:11.217 --> 31:14.742
Goames wanted them
for the Company,

31:14.829 --> 31:16.396
the Company wanted them
to arm the Iroquois.

31:16.483 --> 31:18.659
I don't know what the girl
had to do with it.

31:18.746 --> 31:21.662
He told me to meet them
in the path by the creek.

31:21.749 --> 31:23.229
No, Mathilde. Mathilde!

31:23.316 --> 31:26.319
It's too dangerous
to go at night. Huh?

31:26.406 --> 31:28.756
We'll go at first light.

31:28.843 --> 31:31.411
We'll find her, don't worry.

31:50.909 --> 31:52.911
[branches snapping]

32:20.286 --> 32:21.330
Pistols.

32:44.571 --> 32:45.746
What more do you want?

32:47.661 --> 32:50.359
I have what I came for.

32:50.446 --> 32:52.100
Then take your coin and begone,

32:52.187 --> 32:54.189
before they think better
of the trade.

33:04.417 --> 33:06.375
[insects trilling]

33:20.389 --> 33:22.478
♪ ♪

33:51.377 --> 33:54.945
I thought we might talk.

33:55.033 --> 33:57.209
There is nothing to talk about.

34:02.388 --> 34:04.477
It would be better
if it was settled.

34:06.131 --> 34:08.046
I am just given to Sel.

34:08.133 --> 34:10.309
That is the end of it.

34:13.312 --> 34:14.487
Very well.

34:18.404 --> 34:22.234
Come. Sit.

34:22.321 --> 34:23.496
Have some food.

34:26.412 --> 34:29.676
-I should get back.
-It is not much.

34:29.763 --> 34:32.853
Just some soup.

34:34.594 --> 34:37.205
One last supper,
as we used to do.

34:37.292 --> 34:39.251
[laughs softly]

34:43.516 --> 34:46.388
Yes, I would like that.

35:09.716 --> 35:11.674
[fire crackling]

35:18.072 --> 35:20.422
I cooked our first meal
in this pot.

35:22.816 --> 35:24.513
Yes.

35:24.600 --> 35:28.038
I remember.

35:28.126 --> 35:30.824
When there were only...

35:30.911 --> 35:34.001
trees and rain

35:34.088 --> 35:36.090
pressing down on us.

35:38.266 --> 35:40.138
We made do.

35:42.096 --> 35:43.706
Yes, we did.

35:45.534 --> 35:46.709
You made do.

35:49.973 --> 35:51.845
Yes.

35:51.932 --> 35:54.152
I suppose that is right.

36:01.637 --> 36:04.771
Tell me what the ram augured.

36:09.210 --> 36:11.865
Nothing.

36:11.952 --> 36:14.302
His insides were spoiled.

36:29.752 --> 36:31.885
Go on.

36:31.972 --> 36:34.366
Serve yourself.

36:34.453 --> 36:37.673
You'll have to get used to it.
[chuckles]

36:40.372 --> 36:42.330
Yes.

36:44.637 --> 36:47.379
Yes, of course.

36:47.466 --> 36:49.076
[sniffles]

37:12.969 --> 37:15.363
This is good.

37:18.540 --> 37:20.499
[insects trilling]

37:28.724 --> 37:31.684
[panting]

37:48.831 --> 37:50.833
[panting]

38:20.515 --> 38:22.474
[birds chirping]

38:55.898 --> 38:57.770
♪ ♪

39:25.624 --> 39:27.582
[chickens clucking]

39:32.718 --> 39:35.198
[men speaking French]

39:35.285 --> 39:36.809
MATHILDE:
I am going with you.

39:36.896 --> 39:38.637
It's not safe.

39:38.724 --> 39:41.117
I am going,
and that is the end of it.

39:51.780 --> 39:54.174
-[men yelling, whooping]
-[speaking in Mohawk]

40:10.146 --> 40:12.758
You're going to Wobik,
aren't you?

40:12.845 --> 40:13.846
We had a deal.

40:13.933 --> 40:15.891
That was ourdeal.

40:15.978 --> 40:19.242
But as for the Iroquois,
a man may as well cup his balls

40:19.329 --> 40:21.419
and call lightning down
from the sky.

40:21.506 --> 40:23.812
TEHONIKONHRAKEN:
I don't know how it is
where you are from,

40:23.899 --> 40:26.380
but here, we avenge
the death of our sons.

40:26.467 --> 40:28.208
Well, maybe you would
like to know

40:28.295 --> 40:29.731
who put your son in the tree.

40:33.082 --> 40:35.041
It was the English
who killed your son.

40:35.128 --> 40:37.217
Not the French.

40:40.089 --> 40:42.614
Go on, then. Speak.

40:42.701 --> 40:45.443
It was Bill and Cooke's plan.

40:45.530 --> 40:48.097
They recruited your son
to burn the settlement

40:48.184 --> 40:50.099
along the creek path.

40:50.186 --> 40:53.363
And when they were done
using him, they killed him.

40:53.451 --> 40:55.627
My son was hung
from a tree in Wobik.

40:55.714 --> 40:57.542
Aye.

40:57.629 --> 41:00.022
That wasCaptain Bouchard.

41:00.109 --> 41:02.068
That is true.

41:02.155 --> 41:04.418
But the people of Wobik
are innocent.

41:04.505 --> 41:05.724
Spare them.

41:11.556 --> 41:14.254
I know Bill here is a...

41:14.341 --> 41:15.951
vicious savage.

41:17.257 --> 41:18.911
I always knew that.

41:18.998 --> 41:20.652
But you...

41:22.175 --> 41:23.916
GAY BILL:
We're all savages.

41:24.003 --> 41:25.787
But we're not French.

41:25.874 --> 41:27.615
You will not attack Wobik.

41:27.702 --> 41:29.878
That is not the deal we made.

41:29.965 --> 41:32.446
TEHONIKONHRAKEN:
I will not have two Englishmen
cutting deals for...

41:36.668 --> 41:38.365
Now you have one Englishman.

41:38.452 --> 41:41.847
[groaning]

41:41.934 --> 41:45.633
[speaking in Mohawk]

41:45.720 --> 41:49.507
I want you to draw him
into quarters

41:49.594 --> 41:52.727
-and feed his liver to the dogs.
-[grunting]

42:14.314 --> 42:16.490
MELISSANDE:
Where was he last night?

42:19.058 --> 42:20.189
Mari's.

42:20.276 --> 42:22.278
And now he's dead. Where is she?

42:23.366 --> 42:26.979
I don't know.

42:27.066 --> 42:29.808
-We can't leave him here.
-Why not?

42:29.895 --> 42:32.114
This is the end of everything
for both of us.

42:34.073 --> 42:35.248
He deserves better.

43:03.406 --> 43:05.408
Just take him.

43:09.151 --> 43:11.110
[grunting, gasping]

43:30.042 --> 43:32.000
[grunting]

43:42.228 --> 43:44.099
♪ ♪

44:05.773 --> 44:07.166
[panting]

44:22.442 --> 44:24.444
[Rene grunting]

44:47.772 --> 44:49.730
♪ ♪

45:14.189 --> 45:16.148
MATHILDE [whispers]:
Renardette.

45:19.368 --> 45:21.936
-Renardette.
-[shushes]

45:31.685 --> 45:32.773
What is it?

45:35.689 --> 45:37.386
Take her and go.

45:37.473 --> 45:39.867
I will stand with you.

45:39.954 --> 45:42.043
You will not.
Now run and don't look back

45:42.130 --> 45:44.611
until the creek hits the river.
Go. Go!

45:53.881 --> 45:55.709
DEPUTY:
We have to go, Mathilde.

46:01.454 --> 46:03.238
Come, you savages!

46:04.849 --> 46:07.416
-Come!
-[men yelling, whooping]

46:15.729 --> 46:19.602
[men clamoring, shouting]

46:22.214 --> 46:24.172
[panting]

46:28.437 --> 46:31.136
Go on. Do it.

46:34.574 --> 46:36.576
[grunting]

46:43.496 --> 46:45.890
♪ ♪

47:13.656 --> 47:16.007
Here. You're safe now.

47:21.229 --> 47:23.144
♪ ♪

47:45.253 --> 47:47.212
[indistinct chatter]

47:53.174 --> 47:55.698
♪ ♪

48:10.975 --> 48:12.498
[Delphine exhales]

48:12.585 --> 48:14.543
[distant gunshot]

48:14.630 --> 48:16.589
[people screaming, shouting]

48:20.723 --> 48:22.421
DELPHINE:
What's happening?

48:28.862 --> 48:31.212
This is payment due
for my misdeeds.

48:31.299 --> 48:32.648
[gunfire continues]

48:36.348 --> 48:38.306
[people screaming, shouting]

48:40.352 --> 48:42.267
♪ ♪

48:44.660 --> 48:46.227
[wind whistling]

48:58.674 --> 49:02.156
[gasps]

49:02.243 --> 49:04.202
♪ ♪

